No significant pht main effects or interactive effects between moa and pht were observed for any of the processing yield variables examined. Nevertheless, the means for each of the processing yield variables within the 4 h and 18 h pht treatment groups are provided in Table 1
for observation. There were also no significant main effects due to moa for LBW (P = 0.897), CW (P = 0.729), CLBW (P = 0.139), FPW (P = 0.949), FLBW (P = 0.839), FCW (P = 0.757), BMW (P = 0.425), BMLBW (P = 0.140), BCW (P = 0.222), or TW (P = 0.074) at 49 doa. However, there were significant main effects due to moa for TLBW (P = 0.009) and TCW (P = 0.004). The mean 49 doa values of TLBW and TCW were observed to be higher in the birds that received i.o. injections in comparison to those that received s.c. injections (Table 2
).
